Instructions to run this tool locally

Of course. Here are the instructions for setting up and running the project on your local machine using Visual Studio Code.

Prerequisites
Node.js and npm: Make sure you have Node.js installed. You can download it from nodejs.org.

Visual Studio Code: Download and install VS Code from code.visualstudio.com.

Git: Ensure you have Git installed. You can get it from git-scm.com.

Step-by-Step Guide
1. Create the React Project
Open your terminal (or Command Prompt).

Navigate to the directory where you want to store your project.

Run the following command to create the project:

Bash

npx create-react-app ahp-decision-tool
Navigate into the newly created project folder:

Bash

cd ahp-decision-tool
2. Install Dependencies
Inside the ahp-decision-tool folder, run this command to install the required libraries:

Bash

npm install react-beautiful-dnd react-chartjs-2 chart.js
Next, install the packages needed for Tailwind CSS:

Bash

npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
Generate the Tailwind configuration files:

Bash

npx tailwindcss init -p
3. Add the Project Files
Open the ahp-decision-tool folder in Visual Studio Code.

Using the code from the Canvas, replace the contents of the following files:

package.json

tailwind.config.js

postcss.config.js

public/index.html

src/index.css

src/App.js

4. Run the Application
In your terminal (still inside the project folder), run the start command:

Bash

npm start
This will launch the application in your web browser, typically at http://localhost:3000.
